<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06045039 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06045039 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  In a shake-up of President Bush's stable of speech writers, editorial-pageeditor Tony Snow, 35, of the conservative Washington Times has been hired tobe Bush's principal writer. Bush's advisers have expressed dissatisfactionwith the tone and quality of his speeches. Departing are top speech writerChriss Winston, who says she wants to spend more time with her family, andMark Davis, who has resigned to work for California Gov. Pete Wilson.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  PRESIDENT SHAKES UP SPEECH-WRITING STAFF  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Washington News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910214  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  February  </MONTH><PG.COL>  7A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  78  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday February 14, 199100045039,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>